// Shared signing & identity configuration for Xonora.
//
// Per-developer values (your Apple Developer Team ID, optionally a custom
// bundle identifier) live in Config/Local.xcconfig, which is gitignored so it
// never gets committed. Copy Config/Local.xcconfig.example to
// Config/Local.xcconfig and fill in your details.
//
// The fallback values below are used when Local.xcconfig is absent (e.g. on a
// fresh clone or CI). The `#include?` at the bottom is optional: the build
// still works without a Local.xcconfig — and because it comes last, any value
// you set there overrides the fallbacks here.

// --- Fallback values ---

// Empty by default: with no team set, Xcode falls back to "no team" / manual
// selection. Set DEVELOPMENT_TEAM in Local.xcconfig to your 10-char Team ID.
DEVELOPMENT_TEAM =

// App bundle identifier. Override APP_BUNDLE_ID in Local.xcconfig if
// com.ma.xonora is registered to another team and won't sign under yours.
APP_BUNDLE_ID = com.ma.xonora

// Widget id is always derived from the app id; no need to set it directly.
WIDGET_BUNDLE_ID = $(APP_BUNDLE_ID).XonoraWidget

// App Group id, derived from the app id so it tracks whatever bundle namespace
// you sign under (group.com.chibinet.xonora locally, group.com.ma.xonora as the
// committed fallback). com.ma.* is owned by another team, so a personal account
// can't register group.com.ma.xonora — deriving it from APP_BUNDLE_ID keeps the
// group on a namespace you control. Both targets' entitlements reference
// $(APP_GROUP_ID), and each target's Info.plist exposes it as XonoraAppGroupID so
// XonoraShared.appGroupId can read the resolved value at runtime (app + widget
// must agree on the same group).
APP_GROUP_ID = group.$(APP_BUNDLE_ID)

// --- Per-developer overrides (win over the fallbacks above) ---
#include? "Local.xcconfig"
